==English==
===Noun===
'''wit''' (''plural'' '''wits''')

#Spoken [[humour]], particularly that thought of quickly.
#A person who tells funny anecdotes or jokes.
#(''in plural'' '''wits''') The ability to think quickly.

Aristotle - Wit is educated insolence.

