==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*wid-'', from Indo-European ''*wed-'', a suffixed form of ''*wei-'' (see [[we#Old English|wē]]).  Cognate with Old Norse [[vit]], Gothic [[𐍅𐌹𐍄]], Lithuanian [[vedu|vèdu]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wɪt/

===Personal pronoun===
